Full Title: Association Internationale de Dialectologie Arabe 
Short Title: AIDA 8 

Date: 28-Aug-2008 - 31-Aug-2008
Location: Colchester, Essex, United Kingdom 
Contact Person: Enam Al-Wer
Meeting Email: enama@essex.ac.uk
Web Site: http://www.essex.ac.uk/linguistics/pgr/AIDA/home.shtm 

Linguistic Field(s): General Linguistics 

Call Deadline: 30-Jun-2008 

Meeting Description:

Association Internationale de Dialectologie Arabe (AIDA) 
was set up in Paris in 1993 to provide a forum for Arabic dialectologist. 
Sponsored by the Department of Language and Linguistics, 
University of Essex AIDA 8 convenes in Colchester (UK) 
during 28-31 August 2008. 

Call for Papers

The Local Organising Committee of AIDA 8 welcome abstracts in all areas of linguistics related to Arabic dialects.

Please send abstracts, with title and author's name, app. 300 words in electronic form as an attachment (word format where possible) to the following address:
locaida8@essex.ac.uk

More information and updates can be found at:
http://www.essex.ac.uk/linguistics/pgr/AIDA/home.shtm
 




